# .dockerignore — keep the build context small. The Docker build reaches
# in for source, go.mod/go.sum, policies/, and schemas/; everything else
# is host noise that would only invalidate the build cache.

# Git history.
.git
.gitignore
.github

# Local binaries and build outputs.
/bin/
/dist/
/statebound
/statebound-reason

# Go test/build caches.
*.test
*.out
coverage.txt

# Persistent Go module / build caches mounted by scripts/go.sh.
/.gocache/
/.gomodcache/
/.config/

# Local docker-compose volumes / overrides — irrelevant inside the build
# context and cycles content frequently.
/deploy/docker-compose/.data/
/deploy/docker-compose/docker-compose.override.yml

# Editor / OS noise.
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*~

# Local secrets — never put a credential in a layer.
.env
.env.local
*.pem
*.key

# Generated artifacts, regenerated inside the builder stage.
schemas/openapi.gen.go
schemas/*.gen.go
internal/storage/sqlc/

# Local-only project state.
/.claude/
/.remember/

# ADRs + operating manual stay out of the published image — see
# .gitignore for the policy.
/docs/adr/
/CLAUDE.md

# Helm chart and threat-model docs are not needed inside the image
# itself (they ship in deploy/helm/), but we leave them in the build
# context because the docs are tiny and operators may want to read them
# inside a debug shell. To shrink the context further, uncomment:
# /deploy/helm
# /docs
